ANKARA , Turkey
-LRB- AP -RRB- --
The trial of a former Turkish Cabinet member on charges of aiding and abetting mobsters opened Friday .
Former minister Eyup Asik resigned in September when televisions aired his taped conversations with Turkey 's leading mafia bosses , Alaattin Cakici .
He faces up to a year in prison if convicted .
Asik is a member of Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz ' center-right Motherland Party .
Three no-confidence motions are pending against Yilmaz ' government in connection with the spreading scandal surrounding links between the mafia and the state , and Yilmaz himself is accused of having ties with organized crime .
